<br>
They have a term appropriate to this behavior...no matter how the poster tries to rationalize or qualify it.<br>
<br>
Poor Sportsmanship.<br>
<br>
I am big on this, along with honesty, player respect, courtesy, and setting an example.<br>
The only time it can be overlooked is when you roleplay, and only if others KNOW you are roleplaying. That is REALLY what the /roleplay tag was intended for, not as a /hide function.<br>
<br>
It's a social game...so these things do indeed count, because they affect the game quality for those around you.<br>
 Enough so that I created a guild based on it a couple years ago.<br>
I retired as guildleader due to time constraints about 8 months ago and I'm enjoying my status as guild &quot;old fart&quot;, but the rules still hold strong.<br>
Bad attitudes and behavior degrade the playing experience for all those exposed to it...simple fact, not fiction.<br>
I encourage everyone playing to try and keep this in mind while in Norrath.<br>
<br>
Happy Gaming,<br>
